{
  "texts": [
    "The three teachers and the model rated the texts -half written by humans and half generated by GPT-2 [43] -on a five-point Likert scale in four categories: grammaticality, cohesion, sympathy, and relevance.",
    "The ratings of the teachers and the model only correlated strongly for the criterion relevance, while the other criteria showed a weak positive correlation.",
    "[29] leveraged GPT-3 to evaluate over 12,000 essays from the TOEFL11 dataset [10] across four dimensions: task response, coherence and cohesion, lexical resources, and grammatical range.",
    "They compared GPT-3's performance with 45 linguistic features and discovered that while the linguistic features alone outperformed GPT-3, the combination of both approaches yielded the best results.",
    "Specifically, GPT-3 achieved an accuracy of 54% compared to professional human evaluators but demonstrated an 89% agreement within a deviation of 1 to 2 points."
  ]
}